data.description: Celebrate the new year in this charming 4 bedroom, 2 1/2 bathroom Colonial located in the award-winning Central Bucks School District! This upgraded home is situated on 1.38 acres of manicured grounds in the sought after Amadon neighborhood. A welcoming walkway greets guests and leads to a front foyer entry adorned with decorative moldings. Hardwood flooring extends from the foyer into the dining room and the formal living room—both enhanced by large bay windows providing an abundance of natural light. Step into the heart of the home, a thoroughly upgraded kitchen complimented by a wall of windows overlooking the rear grounds. This special space is further enhanced with custom cabinetry, Taj Mahal quartzite countertops, an oversized island, large pantry, elegant GE Café appliances, a wood sloped range hood & convenient pot filler over the cooktop and a rustic exposed beam that adds additional warmth and character. Recessed lighting and white oak luxury vinyl plank floors enhance the open concept design that seamlessly connects the kitchen, oversized dining area and den—complete with wood-burning stone fireplace and an additional bay window.  A convenient half bath with stylish vanity and a well-appointed mudroom with distressed wood-look tile floor & shiplap and complete the main level. Upstairs, the primary bedroom suite is complimented by a walk-in closet & brand new ensuite with granite vanity & vessel basin and expanded stall shower with horizontal & hexagon tile. Just down the hall are 3 ample bedrooms and an upgraded full bathroom with shiplap and tile floor. The sizable basement has epoxy floors, painted walls and functions well as a game room, den space or gym. Outside, a private rear patio is perfect for your morning coffee, cook-outs & entertaining friends and family. Many improvements and updates have been made during the sellers' ownership, including the installation of a 2nd A/C system, new Riello oil-burning furnace, UV filtration system, aluminum rear fence and much more. Shopping, dining, nightlife and community events are just minutes away in Doylestown Boro & Peddler’s Village and there is easy access to NY and NJ via Route 202. 1-Year Home Warranty included--book your showing today!
